Han ledde Tyskland under den andra världskriget (1939–1945) som krigsherre (Führer). I slutet av 1920-talet grundade han Nationalsocialistiska tyska arbetarepartiet och fick kontroll över Tysklands regering efter att ha vunnit valen i Tyskland år 1933. Han lade ner ett antisemitiskt program med den påstådda judevågen i Tyskland och började en expansionspolitik med Hitlerdoktrinen och annekteringar av Österrike (Anschluss), Tjeckoslovakien och Polska (kallade Sudetenkrisen). Sedan andra världskriget utbröt 1939 valdes han till Tysklands Führer, genom att samla alla maktbefogenheter i en hand genom tredje riksdagen år 1934. Han beslutade att använda sig av kemiska vapen mot ryssarna under Operation Barbarossa år 1941. Trots detta lyckades de ryska styrkorna slå tillbaka den tyska invasionen och började ett motangrepp. Tyskarna återupprättade ett flera arméer i Sovjetunionen år 1942 genom Operation Blau och lyckades driva fram Ryssland längre bort från Europas gränser. Efter Operation Sledgehammer försökte Hitler erövra England men misslyckades efter Operation Sea Lion. In the Novice stage, software developers are just starting to learn the basics of programming and may be struggling with fundamental concepts such as syntax and data types. As they progress through the Advanced Beginner stage, they become more proficient in basic programming concepts and start to develop some creativity in their approach.

The Competent stage is where software developers begin to develop a deep understanding of programming principles and are able to apply them effectively in a variety of contexts. They have a strong foundation in programming concepts and are able to solve common problems with ease.

The Proficient stage is where software developers have mastered the fundamentals of programming and are able to apply them with speed and accuracy. They can handle complex problems and work efficiently with minimal supervision.

Finally, in the Expert stage, software developers have reached the pinnacle of their profession and are considered experts in their field. They have deep insight into programming principles and are able to solve complex problems with ease. They are often sought out for their expertise and leadership skills.

In summary, when it comes to developing expertise in software development, Dreyfus' framework is a useful tool for understanding the stages of development and what is required to progress to each stage.

Here are step-by-step instructions on how to use GitHub for collaborative coding:

Create a GitHub repository: Create a new repository on GitHub, which is a version control system for code projects.
Invite collaborators: Invite other developers to collaborate on the project by sending them an invitation link. They will be able to view and edit the code in the repository.
Fork the repository: Fork the repository you want to collaborate on, which creates a copy of the repository in your own GitHub account.
Clone the forked repository: Clone the forked repository onto your local computer using Git or another version control tool.
Create a branch: Create a new branch in the repository using Git or another version control tool. A branch is a separate line of development within a project.
Collaborate on the branch: Work with your collaborators on the branch, making changes and adding code. When you are ready to merge your changes back into the main branch, follow the steps below.
Merge changes: Merge your changes back into the main branch using Git or another version control tool. This merges your changes with those made by other collaborators, creating a new version of the project.
Push your changes: Push your changes back to the repository on GitHub, which updates the main branch and makes it available to other collaborators.
Review and approve changes: Review and approve changes made by other collaborators before merging them into the main branch. This helps ensure that everyone is on the same page and that no errors or conflicts are introduced during development.
Communicate and collaborate effectively: Communicate effectively with your collaborators through comments, discussions, and pull requests to ensure everyone is working towards the same goal.
source: Skrifaðu skref-fyrir-skref leiðbeiningar um að leysa samrunaátök á GitHub.
